0.8.1 - 2023-01-25
- Squashed a bug using the TAB key.
- Preserves the status of the function keys' line.

0.8 - 2022-08-14
- Speed up milli's init, using a new parameter, /z<n>, where n is the maximum number of lines the file will have.

0.7 - 2022-02-09
- Milli's first stable release. 
- Code polished and reorganized.
- Include file (defs.inc) - organize all variables, constants and special types.
- Fewer local variables, changed to global variables instead.
- We got more 2500 free bytes.
- If you want to know if there is a text block, you may press SELECT+H to unhide it.

0.5 - 2022-01-20
- Now, milli can manage text blocks: mark, copy, move and delete blocks. 
- More bugs squashed.
- Code cleaning, so there are a little more free memory (3 Kb, BTW)

0.3 - 2021-10-04
- There were some bugs in editing mode, so I found some time to fix them. Far from perfect, but it's in a steady walk.

0.2 - 2021-09-09
- Limit increased to text files with 1568 lines and 80 columns - almost all the MSX 2 VRAM.
- Some nasty bugs squashed.

0.1 - 2021-09-04
- First public release.
- Almost all routines runs smoothly.
- Limited to text files with 346 lines with 80 columns each.
